Navbar

#file index.html (only body)
1. create h1 title
2. create nav tag which is known as a navigation element <nav> and set this nav element a class of navbar
3. within <nav>, we’ll create an unordered list that contains list elements
4. we’ll turn a text inside list element into a hyperlink

    <h1>Hello, the Universe</h1>
    <nav class="navbar">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Product</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>  
    </nav>

5. outside the navbar, we’ll use main element for the main content for the web page
6. add h3 and <p> inside the main element

<main>
<h3>This is the Home page</h3>
<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Inventore error culpa nostrum. Quo repellat veniam deserunt assumenda esse harum quod, reiciendis culpa aliquid doloremque magnam quis possimus cum soluta inventore!</p>
</main>

7. link to other files

All Code 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello, the Universe</h1>
    <nav class="navbar">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="main.html">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="About.html">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="Product.html">Product</a></li>
            <li><a href="Contact.html">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>  
    </nav>
    <main>
        <h3>This is the Home page</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Inventore error culpa nostrum. Quo repellat veniam deserunt assumenda esse harum quod, reiciendis culpa aliquid doloremque magnam quis possimus cum soluta inventore!</p>
    </main>    
</body>
</html>


#file style.css
1. add some css properties for h1 element


2. take the navbar class and then select the unordered list to add some css properties


3. take the navbar class and then select the <a> to add some css properties


4. add pseudo-class to <a> 


6. we will make our navbar be horizontal
7. with the navbar class take any list items 
8. and then set overflow to be hidden at .navbar ul{}

All Code
body{
    margin: 0px;
}
main{
    margin: 20px;
}
h1{
    text-align: center;
}
.navbar ul{
    list-style-type: none;
    background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 25%);
    padding: 0px;
    margin: 0px;
    overflow: hidden;
}
.navbar a{
    color:azure;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 15px;
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
}
.navbar a:hover{
    background-color: hsl(0, 0%, 15%);
}
.navbar li{
    float: left;
}

